    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-03-22T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-03-22T15:00:00-05:00" n="826"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d826">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">325.1121 Bethune, Larry K./7: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-22T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 22, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Reference my telegram No. 22, March 19, 4 p.m. <hi rend="italic">Nacion</hi>,
                    Government-owned, quoted editorial from <hi rend="italic">Prensa</hi>, Buenos
                    Aires, and gives substance of editorial from <hi rend="italic">Comercio do</hi>,
                    Lima, criticizing diplomatic intervention in case of General Motors.</p>
                <p>Bethune was not only released but Court of Appeals on a petition in the nature of
                    habeas corpus released his bond. Chilean company has appealed from this decision
                    to Supreme Court. By this action court has recognized justice of Embassy’s
                    protest against illegal arrest. Responsible lawyers state that no possible
                    ground existed under Chilean law for the detention of Bethune.</p>
                <p>Court has decided to appoint a reviewing judge who will take criminal case out of
                    the hands of the Judge of First Instance. Thus the higher court has repudiated
                    the action of the lower judge to which I made objection.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
